<subSubSection id="0E7B5F927A83C0B1BEFBDFB6E9FA8A34" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D1C2E56A211823782A96E4D2FC1705EE" pageNumber="534">
diagnosis Similar in various traits to 
<taxonomicName id="1665F24DB36D11DA0E22C5BE5776D526" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181839" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole angulifera Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole angulifera Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="534" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulifera">angulifera</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="1B8B6AB6C5D78735AA656756BA36FFC3" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181913" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole nitidicollis Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole nitidicollis Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="534" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidicollis">nitidicollis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="9117BE15604EED06E3A0D0C6D983139D" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181870" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole erratilis Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole erratilis Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="534" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erratilis">erratilis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B443D57D7C69710F3D79404330F5AFD2" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181877" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole gilva Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole gilva Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="534" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gilva">gilva</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="11023EA930517A28D01824AA9B69DF4B" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182066" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole polita Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole polita Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="534" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polita">polita</taxonomicName>
(in the 
<taxonomicName id="A1287474CFC92CB00F93FD031E61535F" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34070" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="534" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">tristis</taxonomicName>
group), 
<taxonomicName id="425465A98C2E2FA37E985EE890F2CF9A" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181939" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole schmalzi Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole schmalzi Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="534" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schmalzi">schmalzi</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="BB9D9B415C7D2356A562A4D3072457AB" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181949" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tambopatae Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tambopatae Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="534" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tambopatae">tambopatae</taxonomicName>
, differing as follows. Major: head bicolored as illustrated; median ocellus present; humerus in dorsal-oblique view bearing a rightangular extension; occipital cleft very broad and moderately deep; propodeal spines directed strongly backward; postpetiole very narrow and oval from above; rear quarter of dorsal head surface smooth and shiny.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CC089EFB36647AD0E5EA05462AE5F071" type="description">
<paragraph id="FABD8362E149A8D3065E13E7EB790533" pageNumber="534">Minor: occiput somewhat narrowed, its margin weakly convex, and lacking nuchal collar; propodeal spines directed strongly backward; head almost completely smooth and shiny, with only a few faint carinulae at the antennal fossae; pilosity long, some hairs longer than Eye Length.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="21FFAE2DEC66D17C8AE4ED702C6FC1F4" pageNumber="534">Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 0.74, HL 0.80, SL 0.42, EL 0.10, PW 0.36. Paratype minor: HW 0.42, HL 0.46, SL 0.40, EL 0.12, PW 0.30.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EDEF460C90DC718F37958F8E5D1FF3F3" pageNumber="534">color Major: head bicolored, with vertex and frontal triangle medium brown and rest of head brownish yellow; tarsi brownish yellow; rest of body and appendages light brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C80BE4D588D1AC6953C11D9D219E4148" pageNumber="534">Minor: head and gaster dark brown, tarsi brownish yellow, rest of body and appendages medium brown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E8756F11248A318C877C134E764AC8A9" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="860231F52699EAD76C68A62DF6C97A53" pageNumber="534">range Known only from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
